Briton
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:be a Briton: said to encourage a child to put a brave face on a hurt or setback (hence a (little) Briton, a brave child)


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1935 Havelock said to children who have hurt themselves: also `Be a soldier, now. Don't cry.'
